<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb81e6670-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s3384"><num value="3384">§ 3384.</num><heading> Regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary is authorized to issue regulations to carry out the provisions of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb81e6671-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/92/297/s3/a">Pub. L. 92–297, § 3(a)</ref>, <date date="1972-05-16">May 16, 1972</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/86/143">86 Stat. 143</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/96/347/s1/b">Pub. L. 96–347, § 1(b)</ref>, <date date="1980-09-12">Sept. 12, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/1150">94 Stat. 1150</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb81e6672-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb81e6673-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idb81e6674-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">For definition of Secretary, referred to in text, see <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s2109">section 2109 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idb81e6675-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1980—<ref href="/us/pl/96/347">Pub. L. 96–347</ref> substituted “Secretary” for “Secretary of Transportation”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb81e6676-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="idb81e6677-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1980 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/96/347">Pub. L. 96–347</ref> effective on 90th day after <date date="1980-09-12">Sept. 12, 1980</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/96/347/s3">section 3 of Pub. L. 96–347</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s2109">section 2109 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb81e6678-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective on 90th day after <date date="1972-05-16">May 16, 1972</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/92/297/s10">section 10 of Pub. L. 92–297</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s3381">section 3381 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
